Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.30,0:05:04.30,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Yasue Nagato (32)\NSecond Daughter of\Nthe Nagato Family
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.55,0:07:09.15,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,700)\move(320,330,320,320)\t(0,3600,\fscx76.5\fscy85)}Hideomi Nagato (36)\NEldest Son & Novelist
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.86,0:07:19.90,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuaki Nagato (36)\NYasue's Husband & Head of Nagato Construction
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.49,0:01:46.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What an elegant mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.06,0:01:49.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd expect nothing less from the head of the Nagato Group,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.13,0:01:51.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,which stands equal with Sonoko's family!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.80,0:01:54.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you know Miss Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.64,0:01:59.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She visited a few times when she was a little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.01,0:02:02.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"Miss" doesn't quite fit her, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.05,0:02:05.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why does someone that important want to see you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.32,0:02:09.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He personally asked for the great Kogoro Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.92,0:02:12.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He wants me to solve a big case!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.42,0:02:15.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Or make sure his wife isn't cheating.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.06,0:02:16.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.00,0:02:19.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.66,0:02:22.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are these holes around the pond?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.73,0:02:27.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We plan to plant new trees here by the week's end...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.77,0:02:30.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon my lateness, but I am Take Kuranosuke,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.14,0:02:34.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the family's butler for the last two generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.25,0:02:39.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! The inside is amazing, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.82,0:02:42.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The master waits on the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.29,0:02:47.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There sure are lots of guards...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.89,0:02:50.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally. It's a big case.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.96,0:02:54.90,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh? Haven't I seen him before?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.17,0:03:02.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! Find your first love?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.21,0:03:04.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?! The great Kogoro Mouri?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.95,0:03:06.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.18,0:03:09.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My old friend assured me you could...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.95,0:03:13.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,find her with lightning speed!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.88,0:03:18.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, you didn't need to bring me here just to ask that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.29,0:03:21.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad it wasn't a big case, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.79,0:03:26.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any photos of this woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.56,0:03:30.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. We met during grade school.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.40,0:03:33.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't even remember her face...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.24,0:03:39.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But lately, for some reason,\NI'm reminded of how lovely she was...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.88,0:03:44.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My late wife may not be happy to hear that, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.72,0:03:46.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no photographs,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.42,0:03:50.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I do know her name and her later whereabouts!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.45,0:03:51.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell them, Hyuga{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.96,0:03:53.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.53,0:03:57.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Her name is Kotomi Akagi, from Kanagawa Prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.69,0:04:00.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After graduation, she married at age 29.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.63,0:04:03.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She and husband Kohei Yamato had one child,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.50,0:04:06.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but all three suddenly disappeared five years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.84,0:04:08.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure they didn't flee by night?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.90,0:04:09.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Unthinkable!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.74,0:04:13.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's this old friend who recommended me, anyway?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.88,0:04:15.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.71,0:04:17.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.04,0:04:19.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the old friend I mentioned!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.85,0:04:23.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Osaka's chief of police, Hattori Heizo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.52,0:04:26.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Osaka's chief of police?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.06,0:04:29.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who's always on TV whenever something happens in Osaka?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.89,0:04:32.63,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}l thought he looked familiar...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.63,0:04:35.27,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait! Does that mean—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.27,0:04:38.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Heya, Kudo! How ya been?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.17,0:04:39.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Heiji Hattori?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.77,0:04:40.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.37,0:04:46.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? They still don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.30,0:04:48.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not, you moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.18,0:04:51.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By "Kudo" do you mean—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.18,0:04:55.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I said "Kuro"! As in "thanks for your hard work"!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.18,0:04:55.85,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,go-kurō
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.72,0:05:00.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you have company, Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.76,0:05:04.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's not just guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.83,0:05:07.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A vixen is here, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.97,0:05:11.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told you've been staying here recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.27,0:05:13.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What scheme are you cooking up?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.36,0:05:14.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.97,0:05:18.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, Nobuko! I am unable to move!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.18,0:05:20.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I need her to send notes to the office...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.38,0:05:23.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A fax machine could do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.18,0:05:26.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, it's not that simple...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.18,0:05:28.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are these gentlemen?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.12,0:05:29.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.42,0:05:30.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detectives?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.61,0:05:32.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are detectives here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.52,0:05:36.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He called them here to ask them to find his first—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.26,0:05:40.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody asked you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.03,0:05:41.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.70,0:05:47.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You still have that filthy pen?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.94,0:05:51.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if it's your dad's keepsake! It's creepy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.94,0:05:57.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Better watch out, or she'll steal your Mitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.71,0:05:59.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.15,0:06:02.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Such rudeness!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.52,0:06:04.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize, Hyuga{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.29,0:06:08.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's simply upset that she hasn't found a man yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.93,0:06:11.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.06,0:06:14.43,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I doubt she'll ever find one...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.43,0:06:17.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I should return to the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.10,0:06:21.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Hyuga{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. I'd like to make the announcement tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.31,0:06:24.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so if you do pity my son—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.41,0:06:29.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't pity him at all! This is our fate!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.21,0:06:33.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A "bond of flames" has connected us for a long time now...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.55,0:06:35.61,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Bond of flames?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.32,0:06:44.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You two were in the same kendo club?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.46,0:06:49.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Nagato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} used to beat me down like a demon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.33,0:06:52.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, Heizo. About the matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.00,0:06:56.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I had the guards double-check, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.51,0:07:00.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who're you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.72,0:07:03.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My son, Hideomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.48,0:07:07.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His face was burned in an accident long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.38,0:07:09.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since, he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.72,0:07:13.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think modern plastic surgery could fix most of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.52,0:07:15.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he's against the idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.86,0:07:21.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's a happy ending, all thanks to the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.83,0:07:23.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Hideomi?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.07,0:07:29.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hideomi! Wait! What're you so mad for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.71,0:07:37.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish you a happy birthday, Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.98,0:07:39.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.25,0:07:45.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd appreciate it if you'd give me the title of president in return...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.82,0:07:50.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.33,0:07:52.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I must be getting back to Osaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.60,0:07:57.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? You're not going to celebrate with us tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.77,0:07:59.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's also the matter at hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.20,0:08:03.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's alright. I'll be leaving him in my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.94,0:08:07.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's still green, but he's got good intuition.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.84,0:08:11.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he'll be of use to Detective Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.35,0:08:12.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Use?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.52,0:08:21.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy birthday, Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.65,0:08:24.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy birthday, Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.29,0:08:28.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to use this opportunity to make an announcement.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.07,0:08:33.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My son Hideomi and Miyuki Hyuga{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nare engaged to be married!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.07,0:08:33.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.94,0:08:36.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this true, Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.34,0:08:42.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I've been having her stay here so she would grow used to the house!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.95,0:08:45.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so that's why!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.78,0:08:49.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Where is Nobuko-{\i1}ojōsama{\i0} going?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.29,0:08:51.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mind her!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.22,0:08:55.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's just the only single person left!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.73,0:08:59.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, I don't see Hideomi...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.23,0:09:02.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's probably embarrassed. I'll go get him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.74,0:09:13.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Hattori! Out with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.04,0:09:13.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Out with what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.81,0:09:18.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The real reason you brought us here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.48,0:09:22.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like that! I just wanted to see ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.75,0:09:25.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Liar...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.36,0:09:27.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding! The truth is—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.36,0:09:31.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.50,0:09:34.90,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is Mitsuaki. Could you put my father on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.90,0:09:41.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's asleep at the moment. We're just about to leave...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.20,0:09:44.01,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I can't find Hideomi anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.01,0:09:45.84,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Where the heck did he—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.91,0:09:50.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.11,0:09:52.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?! Where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.53,0:09:54.15,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Right below you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.15,0:09:57.35,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Someone cut the lights and attacked me with—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.46,0:10:03.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Are you alright?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.93,0:10:07.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! What's going on?! Mitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.73,0:10:11.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.17,0:10:15.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We gotta stop him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.28,0:10:21.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No... why would he...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.81,0:10:26.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! It's locked from the inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.19,0:10:27.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get the master key!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.92,0:10:28.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.50,0:10:29.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.62,0:10:31.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll check around outside with the guards!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.56,0:10:39.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! What's going on?! Mitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.26,0:10:43.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective! Here's the key!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.67,0:10:46.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's empty!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.36,0:10:48.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.37,0:10:51.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! He used a rope to escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.42,0:10:53.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But where's Mitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.15,0:10:57.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's there. Down below.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.69,0:11:09.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, he fell onto the fence...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.49,0:11:14.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true that the killer is\NMr. Nagato's son, Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.50,0:11:16.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.40,0:11:22.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't do it! There must be some reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.17,0:11:25.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's still a murderer, whatever the reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.64,0:11:29.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Give my Mitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} back...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.15,0:11:32.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would never do this...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.62,0:11:36.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, we don't know he's the person we saw!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.25,0:11:37.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.03,0:11:38.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.32,0:11:41.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We only saw someone with bandages on their face.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.86,0:11:42.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Bandages?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.88,0:11:44.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.03,0:11:47.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had burn scars all over his face...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.20,0:11:49.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw the killer shortly after 10:00 PM,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.80,0:11:54.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when everyone happened to be\Nin the third-story bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.54,0:11:55.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Everyone" being...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.97,0:12:05.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Me, Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, Ran, Conan, Take{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} the butler, and Yasue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.12,0:12:07.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do when they left?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.59,0:12:10.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I stayed in the room with the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.72,0:12:18.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To think the killer prepared that grappling hook to escape...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.33,0:12:22.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no question that the killer used it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.50,0:12:26.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was still swaying when we checked around outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.54,0:12:29.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And where's Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.01,0:12:32.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's nowhere to be seen...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.21,0:12:36.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We looked for him while the police were on their way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.15,0:12:38.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is clearly the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.97,0:12:40.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.52,0:12:46.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, we've found the killer's weapon, hat, and bandages.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.49,0:12:47.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Analysis should prove—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.73,0:12:48.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.63,0:12:55.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this on his right hand?\NIt's like he was stabbed by something...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.97,0:13:04.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably from the knife or the fence he fell on!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.44,0:13:05.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.78,0:13:07.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.51,0:13:14.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The exterior security cameras show nobody leaving after the murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.99,0:13:16.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the killer's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.99,0:13:19.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...still in the mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.56,0:13:20.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh, no!\N- Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.89,0:13:22.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The president!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.34,0:13:24.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! He's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.93,0:13:31.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! It's locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.67,0:13:34.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Anyone in there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.47,0:13:36.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's all the ruckus?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.61,0:13:39.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with you all?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.24,0:13:41.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.55,0:13:45.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to see what all the noise was about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.35,0:13:48.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you before then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.52,0:13:52.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was irritated, so I had a drink in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.92,0:13:54.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.13,0:13:58.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. While complaining to a friend on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.30,0:14:01.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be the alcohol,\Nbut I can't recall who it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.97,0:14:05.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, is it true that Hideomi killed Mitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.97,0:14:07.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, most likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.84,0:14:11.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I figured he would eventually...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.21,0:14:17.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Those two would fight\Nevery time they saw each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.75,0:14:21.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They seemed to be friends since childhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.99,0:14:24.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but they were like cat and dog after the incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.86,0:14:26.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.52,0:14:31.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. There was a big fire\Nat a nearby inn 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.86,0:14:36.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hideomi and Mitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nhigh-schoolers at the time, passed by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.83,0:14:43.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} tried to stop him,\Nbut Hideomi plunged into the flames
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.01,0:14:45.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and rescued a little girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.94,0:14:49.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki Hyuga, to be precise!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.85,0:14:53.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ah, hence the "bond of flames."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.85,0:14:57.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hideomi's face was burned as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.25,0:15:00.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, he quit school, shut himself in his room,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.62,0:15:03.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and pretended to write novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.53,0:15:06.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No women got near him, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.10,0:15:09.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She used that to make a pass at him,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.97,0:15:12.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,get recommended as Father's secretary,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.74,0:15:15.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and even marry into the family!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.41,0:15:18.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough, Nobuko.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.18,0:15:21.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.55,0:15:25.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ever since everyone left the room in an uproar,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.45,0:15:27.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,though things have been fuzzy...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.85,0:15:30.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anything strange happen afterward?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.72,0:15:37.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing at all. Hyuga{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} stayed with me until Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.39,0:15:43.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, this is no time to look for your first love now...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.13,0:15:47.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it isn't. Please forget about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.01,0:15:56.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me already! Why'd you bring me here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.25,0:15:57.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.85,0:16:02.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, the president said\Nhe heard strange sounds last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.62,0:16:04.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Strange sounds?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.06,0:16:04.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.96,0:16:08.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone sprinting through the hall in the middle of the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.53,0:16:12.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and something hitting something else, lots of times!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.76,0:16:14.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it have been—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.50,0:16:16.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Someone inside the house
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.63,0:16:21.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was doing something for tonight's murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.64,0:16:26.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Me and my old man figured it was a burglar scoping the place out,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.44,0:16:29.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so we brought in security and called you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.11,0:16:31.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We thought he'd show up again tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.82,0:16:36.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but it was a life that was taken!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.25,0:16:38.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A premeditated murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.19,0:16:41.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But doesn't it seem strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.33,0:16:45.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That Kogoro Mouri guy you made famous was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.83,0:16:50.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer musta been really confident with his plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.33,0:16:54.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Or, he couldn't{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge his plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.17,0:16:59.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What bothers me are the killer's items that were lying by the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.24,0:17:05.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no need to drop the hat or bandages, never mind the weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.75,0:17:10.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the way the killer purposely showed his face to us...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.69,0:17:14.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Almost as if to frame Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.12,0:17:20.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only one who coulda done that is Nobuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who left beforehand!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.30,0:17:27.64,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We then searched every nook and cranny of the mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.64,0:17:30.54,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}but Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Narration Off}-san{\r} was nowhere to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.54,0:17:35.60,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We were all about to give up two evenings later, when...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.88,0:17:38.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't find him anywhere, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.43,0:17:39.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.98,0:17:42.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault Hideomi never married?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.89,0:17:47.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, are you saying he held back for me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.22,0:17:51.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I just meant that he thought highly of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.67,0:17:57.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.03,0:18:00.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop! That pond is deep!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.00,0:18:05.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that pen is my father's keepsake! Without it, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.28,0:18:07.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Drain the water, quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.05,0:18:08.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.58,0:18:14.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is one filthy pond...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.35,0:18:19.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam kept carp in it,\Nbut once she passed away...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.14,0:18:36.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?! Why did this have to happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.77,0:18:39.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother! Hideo-{\i1}oniisama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.78,0:18:42.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is his estimated time of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.48,0:18:47.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been dead for approximately 1.5 to 2 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.58,0:18:50.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was pushed off the balcony
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.69,0:18:54.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,at 10:00 the night before last, 44 hours ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.59,0:18:58.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} drowned himself in this pond before we arrived,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.90,0:19:03.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,everything would fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.37,0:19:06.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,However, he didn't drown to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.50,0:19:09.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't be sure until the autopsy,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.14,0:19:13.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he likely ingested poison before entering the pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.85,0:19:20.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The body didn't float up because of these rocks in his clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.38,0:19:25.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} carried the rocks into the pond and poisoned himself?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.46,0:19:29.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably didn't want anyone to see him dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.26,0:19:33.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, as hostile as Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and\NMitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were with each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.43,0:19:35.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,murder is a bit much...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.80,0:19:42.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible. Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} and\NYasue-{\i1}ojōsama{\i0} were very close,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.57,0:19:49.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so he was vehemently against her marriage with Mitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.91,0:19:54.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So he couldn't stomach the idea of losing his dear little sister
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.32,0:19:56.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to his bad friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.39,0:19:57.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Foolish child...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.89,0:20:01.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure! Here's the lab report!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.09,0:20:01.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.88,0:20:02.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.56,0:20:07.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"The marks on the knife match\Nthe wounds on Mitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s arm,"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.33,0:20:11.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"and the blood on the knife matches his as well."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.50,0:20:18.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"The hair follicles in the hat and bandages\Nbelong to Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.34,0:20:21.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me, there was\Na meter-long grappling hook
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.35,0:20:23.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,in Mitsuaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s jacket pocket...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.68,0:20:25.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A grappling hook?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.28,0:20:28.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was the cut on his right hand from the knife, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.62,0:20:30.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it was different...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.35,0:20:34.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the blood type of the saliva on the knife?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.22,0:20:37.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There wasn't any. Seems it was wiped off...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.03,0:20:44.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector! I found this paper in his pocket!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.24,0:20:48.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm not fit to marry you..."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.34,0:20:52.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I choose death to atone for the sin I committed."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.98,0:20:58.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is his will! Miyuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! It's addressed to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.05,0:20:59.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s handwriting?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.85,0:21:02.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it looks like it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.05,0:21:06.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get some of his writings from his room...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.26,0:21:11.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Here's the pen you dropped in...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.86,0:21:14.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.67,0:21:16.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let her be.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.47,0:21:20.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give it to her later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.51,0:21:26.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.84,0:21:31.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This pen's really been burnt...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.48,0:21:32.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.74,0:21:35.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. This case is totally weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.72,0:21:38.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even more unnatural is that will.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.38,0:21:42.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It said, "The sin I committed."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.29,0:21:46.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning he wrote it after the murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.43,0:21:49.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't have time to write a will then!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.50,0:21:54.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means someone forged it or forced him to write it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.30,0:21:57.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, there's little doubt that someone drowned him
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.67,0:22:00.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with the will after poisoning him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.94,0:22:04.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, the only time anyone got near the pond
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.45,0:22:07.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was when we all went looking for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.65,0:22:13.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had been murdered before it happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.82,0:23:48.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Don't tell me Hideomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was actually—
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.22,0:23:51.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right! His estimated time of death was...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.66,0:23:57.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, there was a way, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.33,0:23:59.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Hattori.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.30,0:24:03.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever killed someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.21,0:24:09.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.61,0:24:14.53,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.53,0:24:19.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint: Fountain Pen
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.66,0:24:20.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Next time, it's—
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.40,0:24:22.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}- case...\N- case...\N- case...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.21,0:24:24.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}...case closed!
